---
import PageHeader from '../components/PageHeader.astro';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="How this AI portfolio fits beside Min Wen's main blog."
>
  <PageHeader
    eyebrow="About"
    title="A small place for AI artifacts, not another blog."
    description="The main blog stays the home for long writing. This project keeps images and experiments easy to publish, browse, and revisit."
  />
  <section
    class="mx-auto grid max-w-7xl gap-10 px-5 pb-20 lg:grid-cols-3 lg:px-8"
  >
    <div class="prose-lab lg:col-span-2">
      <h2>Process</h2>
      <p>
        The default workflow is intentionally small: copy generated images into
        <code>incoming/images</code>, then run the site. Automation creates the
        optimized media, thumbnail, and landing-page MDX entry.
      </p>
      <p>
        When something deserves more care, the generated MDX can be edited into
        a fuller note with prompt details, tools, tags, and provenance.
      </p>
      <h2>Main blog</h2>
      <p>
        Longer posts, search, tags, and personal context live at
        <a href="https://cmwen.github.io/">cmwen.github.io</a>. This site points
        back there instead of trying to duplicate that structure.
      </p>
      <h2>Licensing</h2>
      <p>
        Generated entries default to CC BY-NC 4.0 unless noted otherwise.
        Replace that value when a source tool, model, or project needs different
        usage notes.
      </p>
      <h2>Provenance</h2>
      <p>
        Auto-imported images include the source filename and a SHA-256 checksum
        so later cleanup can tell what came from which local file.
      </p>
    </div>
    <aside
      class="rounded-lg border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface)] p-6"
    >
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold">V1 principles</h2>
      <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm leading-6 text-[var(--muted)]">
        <li>Main blog remains the hub.</li>
        <li>Images can start with almost no manual metadata.</li>
        <li>Generated records are editable when needed.</li>
        <li>Small static output stays easy to host on GitHub Pages.</li>
      </ul>
    </aside>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
